+---
+title: Biotechnology
+description: PFT biotechnology projects connect biological complexity with measurable, useful outcomes.
+key: biotechnology
+eyebrow: Sector 02 / Biotechnology
+heroTitle: From biological complexity to <em>useful systems.</em>
+heroText: Biology gives us extraordinary possibilities. The work is making them measurable, understandable and ready to matter outside the lab.
+shortCode: BIO
+visualWord: life
+visualLabel: Biological systems
+visualLabels:
+  one: observe
+  two: understand
+  three: apply
+introTitle: Science becomes powerful when it can travel.
+introText: PFT explores the bridge between biological research, engineering discipline and products that can be used in the field, the clinic or the community.
+focus:
+  - title: Medical devices
+    text: Translating biological and clinical insight into products with a clear purpose and path to use.
+    tag: Applied science
+    mark: ◉
+  - title: Agri-bio
+    text: Earlier, better information for biological systems that feed, sustain and shape the world around us.
+    tag: Field intelligence
+    mark: ✳
+  - title: Living systems
+    text: Tissue engineering, genetics and the tools that help us work with biological complexity rather than hide it.
+    tag: Frontier work
+    mark: ≋
+featureKicker: Biotechnology / direction 01
+featureTitle: Make biology legible.
+featureText: A concept space for translating experiments, measurements and biological variation into decisions people can actually use.
+featureStatus: Early direction
+featureCode: PFT—BIO—01
+featureList:
+  - grounded in real biological constraints
+  - designed for repeatable measurement
+  - built with the path to adoption in mind
+principlesTitle: Respect the science. Build for the world.
+principles:
+  - title: Evidence matters
+    text: Strong claims need strong foundations, honest limits and room for uncertainty.
+  - title: Translation is a craft
+    text: The last mile between discovery and use deserves as much thought as the first.
+  - title: Outcomes compound
+    text: Better measurement today can unlock better questions tomorrow.
+ctaTitle: Working on a biological problem<br><em>that needs a bridge?</em>
+---
