+---
+title: Enterprise
+description: PFT enterprise projects improve the operating systems that help teams deliver useful work.
+key: enterprise
+eyebrow: Sector 03 / Enterprise
+heroTitle: Operational clarity is a <em>product.</em>
+heroText: The right system makes good work easier to repeat, easier to govern and easier for a team to move forward with confidence.
+shortCode: ENT
+visualWord: flow
+visualLabel: Operating systems
+visualLabels:
+  one: map
+  two: simplify
+  three: deliver
+introTitle: Small improvements can change the shape of a business.
+introText: From compliance-ready foundations to product architecture, PFT works on the quiet systems that turn ambition into consistent execution.
+focus:
+  - title: Compliance kits
+    text: Practical structures for risk, documentation, training and the evidence a growing business needs.
+    tag: Ready to operate
+    mark: ✓
+  - title: Product architecture
+    text: Clearer relationships between the customer, the workflow, the technology and the business model.
+    tag: Systems thinking
+    mark: □
+  - title: Workflow design
+    text: Removing friction from the work people actually do — and making the improvement stick.
+    tag: Better operations
+    mark: ↗
+featureKicker: Enterprise / direction 01
+featureTitle: Give good work a better operating system.
+featureText: A concept space for lightweight systems, documentation and tooling that help small teams operate with the clarity of a much larger one.
+featureStatus: Framework / building
+featureCode: PFT—ENT—01
+featureList:
+  - proportionate to the team using it
+  - clear enough to teach and hand over
+  - resilient when the business changes
+principlesTitle: Make the invisible work visible.
+principles:
+  - title: Reduce ambiguity
+    text: A good system makes the next action, owner and decision easier to see.
+  - title: Keep it proportionate
+    text: Governance should create confidence, not a second job nobody can maintain.
+  - title: Design for handover
+    text: The best operating system is one the team can own after the builder leaves.
+ctaTitle: Is the way you work<br><em>harder than it needs to be?</em>
+---
